From: "Barak A. Pearlmutter" <barak+git@pearlmutter.net>
Date: Mon, 2 Feb 2026 12:35:10 +0000
Subject: Use appstreamcli instead of appstream-util when available

Debian has switched from appstream-util to appstreamcli, other
platforms are lagging but will likely switch in due course. Therefore
switch the CI build dependency where possible, and scan for both
dynamically, preferring appstreamcli when both are available but
falling back to appstream-util if necessary. Also emit a warning if
neither is found.

See https://bugs.debian.org/1119105

See https://github.com/transmission-remote-gtk/transmission-remote-gtk/issues/269
---
 .github/workflows/c-cpp.yml |  2 +-
 README.md                   |  4 ++--
 data/meson.build            | 19 +++++++++++++++++--
 3 files changed, 20 insertions(+), 5 deletions(-)

diff --git a/.github/workflows/c-cpp.yml b/.github/workflows/c-cpp.yml
index 48d3b43..9cc2b06 100644
--- a/.github/workflows/c-cpp.yml
+++ b/.github/workflows/c-cpp.yml
@@ -22,7 +22,7 @@ jobs:
                                gettext \
                                \
                                libappstream-dev \
-                               appstream-util
+                               appstream
       - name: meson configure
         run: meson setup build
       - name: build
diff --git a/README.md b/README.md
index 93aae4a..8e9b349 100644
--- a/README.md
+++ b/README.md
@@ -36,14 +36,14 @@ transmission-remote-gtk uses meson for its build system. A relatively new
 version of meson is required.
 
  - meson >= 0.59.0
- - appstream-util (optional, appdata validation)
+ - appstream (optional, appdata validation using `appstreamcli validate`)
  - desktop-file-utils (optional, desktop file validation)
  - rst2man (optional, manpage generation)
 
 An example of getting the build dependencies for an Ubuntu/Debian system:
 
 ```
-# apt install gcc meson appstream-util python-docutils
+# apt install gcc meson appstream python-docutils
 ```
 
 **NOTE:** Ubuntu and other stable or LTS distros may have outdated versions of
diff --git a/data/meson.build b/data/meson.build
index 70a4799..77b6d77 100644
--- a/data/meson.build
+++ b/data/meson.build
@@ -75,11 +75,26 @@ appdata_file = i18n.merge_file(
   po_dir: po_dir,
 )
 
+# validate appdata
+#
+# Note: appstream-util is deprecated on Debian GNU/Linux, which is switching to appstreamcli.
+#  However appstreamcli is not yet available through brew on MacOS or pacman Microsoft Windows.
+#  Therefore, to future-proof this we use whatever is available, preferring appstreamcli.
+#
+appstreamcli = find_program('appstreamcli', required: false)
 appstream_util = find_program('appstream-util', required: false)
-if appstream_util.found()
+if appstreamcli.found()
+  test(
+    'Validate appdata.xml',
+    appstreamcli,
+    args: ['validate', '--pedantic', '--explain', '--no-net', appdata_file],
+  )
+elif appstream_util.found()
   test(
     'Validate appdata.xml',
     appstream_util,
     args: ['validate-relax', '--nonet', appdata_file],
   )
-endif
\ No newline at end of file
+else
+  warning('Neither appstreamcli nor appstream-util found; skipping appdata.xml validation')
+endif
